rComments: Best prof I've ever had. Period.
awesome
The most beautiful and wonderful prof alive, I don't think he teaches anymore but he definitely should cause he's so amazing

Ron was one of the profs who inspired me to come to UofT (after seeing him on TVO's The Agenda), but was probably the most disappointing prof I've had.  Presents the same material year after year. no novelty in the delivery of course.  the assignment was a massive (30 page) joke, and exams were marked way too hard (an expert wouldn't get an A)

extremely boring and non-engaging. kind of all over the place and doesn't communicate ideas clearly at all. should not be a prof. however, he is extremely knowledgeable about his material - just doesn't know how to teach.
talks a lot about himself. very knowledgable, loves his field of research, but explains complicated computer concepts way too fast often confusing the students.

Great fun for a first class of first year at University. You dont really need to attend many classes to do well in the class but I only went to class when Deibert was teaching, Stein was a bit slow compared to him.
Fantastically brilliant.

Awesome. When I took this course, Stein got all the credit but was hardly ever there. And when she was, her power point lectures were really boring. Deibert spiced it up with his sense of humour and innovative teaching style. I thought he was super.
No Comments
Over simplifies concepts, then over complicates.
An intellectually stimulating professor, who keeps you interested and makes you want to learn.  Too bad he doesn't teach other POL SCI courses
He tries to approach the course at our level - acting like a university student rather than a prof. His slides are more helpful than Stein's, but sometimes he goes too quickly.
hes cool, but the material is totally boring and pointless

This prof is pretty funny. He plays rap music before class and during break. He provides good slides, sometimes goes a little fast but overall if a good solid prof. The class (pol108) is really interesting and overall pretty good. Deibert and Stein make an interesting teching duo, tho you'll definately be seeing more of Deibert than Stein.
Interesting Professor.  Highly enthusiastic guy who makes the lectures fun!
I have the highest most respect for this professor. He's soooo awesome!! He found the perfect balance between entertainment and education! Major props to this guy!
Amazing prof, very funny, made what might be seen as boring material into a lecture that was like going to movie with many interesting facts along added along the way

Deibert was the man!  Its unfortunate we only got him fors half the year.  He was funny, and did anyone notice how he semi-imposed his face on people it the pictures that were the backgrounds for his slides? Hilarious.
Great teacher!

Though Deibert does a lot of moral work around the globe which I commend him for, he doesn't seem to care about giving lectures. The lectures sprawl across a number of topics and the weekly readings are infrequently mentioned. He's a joker with an undergraduate's ironic sense of humour.
No Comments

Wow wat a fun class.  The prof can keep the material pretty situlating, and the 2hr class goes pretty quickly due to it.  Have missed him since he is on leave due to the ilness of his wife.  You have my well wishes man, and hope you return back to what you do best.  Inspire boyz to become men.

Innovative thinker, funny speaker. Though most of what you'll need to know for exams is either in the textbook or the slides available on the web site, if you want to impress your marker take note of Deibert's side notes during his lectures.
Professor Deibert is fun and engaging. He also teaches some good stuff.
the guy is inspirational.  anybody who says otherwise simply doesn't take the stuff seriously.  my life has been changed
as much as the course is a joke, he is the punchline. he uses flashy, gag-tactics in an attempt to win over the adoration of his audience, and you either buy it or you don't.
he was down to earth, clear and intriguing. he was totally about making us feel at ease and if you listened to him, instead of hating on him, you'd see how clever he was. BIG THUMBS up!

he makes class fun, but he constantly changes topic and keeps talking how he was in college and where he's been and who he knows (my friend so and so...)... like i dont pay money to heard him talk about his life.. very disinterested to be honest.
